<li> Apply direct pressure using a clean cloth or sterile dressing directly on the wound.</li>
<li> Do not take out any object that is lodged in a wound. See a doctor for help in removal.</li>
<li> If there are no signs of a fracture in the injured area, carefully elevate the wound above the victim's heart.</li>
<li> Once bleeding is controlled, keep the victim warm by covering with a blanket, continuing to monitor for the shock.</li>
